Quartz is the static-site generator that builds the wiki (EPIC-013): reads
the same story Markdown the board reads (via scripts/build-wiki-content.mjs,
original code, which also injects a `[[wikilink]]`-rendered "At a glance"
section per story so the depends_on/blocks/related/epic graph edges --
frontmatter-only in stories/*.md -- become real navigable links, since
Quartz's own wikilink/backlink resolution only looks at body text). Output
is fully static HTML/CSS/JS; no server-side runtime or database beyond the
one-time build step the Gitea post-receive hook runs on every push.

